    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="711"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d711">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">122.352/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 20, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Your despatch 2462, December 5. The Department is inclined to consider
                    favorably the requests of the Chinese Government contained <pb facs="0730"
                        n="632" xml:id="pg_632"/> in its note of September 23 last.<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d711fn6">Not printed.</note> However, the Department recognizes that
                    disadvantages might readily ensue from compliance with these requests and before
                    coming to a definite decision the Department desires that you endeavor to obtain
                    additional information regarding the views held and position likely to be taken
                    by the other Governments most concerned. You are authorized to intimate to your
                    colleagues in your discretion that this Government is not aware of convincing
                    objections from a technical standpoint that could be made to the Chinese
                    Government’s requests in this connection. Reply by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
